[Our thanks to Ramon for this report. A 'partido' is a 2nd level administrative division, in this case equivalent to a county or district, within the province.

Yet again we can see how unvaccinated stock in an enzootic area maintain awareness of the risk of this disease.

For a map of Argentina showing the province of Buenos Aires, go to http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/argentina_pol96.jpg
To find Pila on the eastern side of the province, go to http://www.fallingrain.com/world/AR/01/Pila.html. - Mod.MHJ]
